{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RSNKsJ9LwH8tq4QtDRv8zk","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have all the information needed. Let me compile a thorough exploration report:\n\n## Visual Test Setup Exploration Report\n\nI've thoroughly explored the visual test infrastructure in the rng-utopia project. Here's a comprehensive breakdown:\n\n### 1. **Directory Structure**\n\n```\nsources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/\n├── e2e/\n│   ├── visual/                          # Visual tests (Playwright)\n│   │   ├── routes.spec.ts               # Route baseline tests\n│   │   └── states.spec.ts               # State variant tests (wallet connection, interactions)\n│   ├── __snapshots__/\n│   │   └── visual/\n│   │       ├── routes.spec.ts/          # Route baselines\n│   │       │   ├── home.png\n│   │       │   ├── coinflip.png\n│   │       │   ├── lord-of-rngs.png\n│   │       │   ├── close-call.png       # Close-Call baseline EXISTS\n│   │       │   ├── crash.png\n│   │       │   ├── game-of-trades.png\n│   │       │   ├── profile.png\n│   │       │   ├── quests.png\n│   │       │   ├── loot.png\n│   │       │   ├── fairness.png\n│   │       │   ├── leaderboard.png\n│   │       │   └── 404.png\n│   │       └── states.spec.ts/          # State variant baselines\n│   │           ├── home-connected.png\n│   │           ├── home-disconnected.png\n│   │           ├── coinflip-connected.png\n│   │           ├── coinflip-disconnected.png\n│   │           ├── coinflip-error-toast-position.png\n│   │           ├── profile-connected.png\n│   │           ├── lotr-*.png (5 variants)\n│   │           └── (No close-call state tests yet)\n│   ├── devnet/                          # Devnet E2E tests (separate config)\n│   ├── local/                           # Local E2E tests (separate config)\n│   ├── real/                            # Real wallet mode tests (separate config)\n│   ├── fixtures.ts                      # Shared visual test utilities\n│   └── __snapshots__/                   # Snapshot storage\n├── playwright.config.ts                 # Visual test config (mock mode)\n├── playwright.real.config.ts            # Real wallet mode config\n├── playwright.local.config.ts           # Local devnet config\n├── playwright.devnet.config.ts          # Devnet config\n└── package.json                         # Scripts\n```\n\n### 2. **Test Runner: Playwright**\n\n- **Framework**: Playwright Test\n- **Browser**: Chromium (Desktop Chrome)\n- **Viewport**: 1280×1080 fixed\n- **Workers**: 1 (sequential, not parallel)\n\n### 3. **Baseline Storage**\n\n- **Location**: `apps/platform/e2e/__snapshots__/visual/{testFilePath}/{arg}.png`\n- **Pattern**: Playwright's default snapshot path template\n- **Organization**: Grouped by spec file (`routes.spec.ts/`, `states.spec.ts/`)\n- **Naming**: Descriptive kebab-case (`close-call.png`, `home-connected.png`, etc.)\n- **Image Baselines**: PNG format, stored in git\n\n### 4. **Test Script Commands**\n\n**In `apps/platform/package.json`:**\n```json\n\"test:visual\": \"playwright test\"\n\"test:visual:update\": \"playwright test --update-snapshots\"\n```\n\n**In root `package.json`:**\n```json\n\"test:visual\": \"turbo run test:visual --env-mode=loose\"\n```\n\n**Usage:**\n- **Run tests (compare against baselines)**: `pnpm test:visual` from root or `pnpm test:visual` from `apps/platform/`\n- **Update baselines**: `pnpm test:visual:update` (only when intentionally changing visuals per memory policy)\n\n### 5. **Close-Call Visual Tests**\n\n**Existing tests:**\n- ✅ **Route baseline**: `routes.spec.ts` has `test(\"close call page\", ...)` that navigates to `/close-call` and captures `close-call.png`\n- ✅ **Baseline image**: Exists at `__snapshots__/visual/routes.spec.ts/close-call.png` (165 KB, last updated 2026-03-10)\n- ❌ **State variants**: NO close-call state tests in `states.spec.ts` (only home, profile, lord-of-rngs, coinflip)\n\n### 6. **Test Configuration (`playwright.config.ts`)**\n\n```typescript\n{\n  testDir: \"./e2e\",\n  fullyParallel: true,           // Tests marked for parallel, but...\n  workers: 1,                    // ...actually runs sequentially (determinism)\n  forbidOnly: !!process.env.CI,  // Fail if .only is left in CI\n  retries: 0,                    // No retries (snapshot matches must be stable)\n  \n  snapshotPathTemplate: \"{testDir}/__snapshots__/{testFilePath}/{arg}{ext}\",\n  \n  expect: {\n    toHaveScreenshot: {\n      maxDiffPixelRatio: 0.015   # 1.5% pixel diff tolerance by default\n    }\n  },\n  \n  projects: [\n    {\n      name: \"chromium\",\n      testMatch: \"visual/**/*.spec.ts\",  # Only matches e2e/visual/*.spec.ts\n      viewport: { width: 1280, height: 1080 }\n    }\n  ],\n  \n  webServer: {\n    command: `npx vite --port 3000`,\n    url: \"http://127.0.0.1:3000\",\n    env: {\n      VITE_MOCK_MODE: \"true\"     # Runs in mock wallet mode\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### 7. **Shared Fixture: `fixtures.ts`**\n\nCustom `stablePage` fixture with deterministic visual testing:\n\n**Determinism mechanisms:**\n- ✅ **Seeded PRNG**: Math.random() uses Mulberry32 with seed 42 (same sequence every run)\n- ✅ **Seeded crypto**: crypto.getRandomValues() seeded for deterministic Keypairs\n- ✅ **Frozen time**: Date.now() frozen to 2026-01-01T00:00:00Z (1767225600000)\n- ✅ **Animation freeze**: All CSS animations/transitions disabled (duration 0s)\n- ✅ **SVG animations paused**: svg.pauseAnimations() called on all SVG elements\n- ✅ **Font loading**: Waits for document.fonts.ready before capturing\n- ✅ **Network idle**: All navigations wait for \"networkidle\" status\n\n**Error handling:**\n- ✅ **Console error filtering**: Tracks console.error() calls with NOISE_PATTERNS:\n  - `401`, `403`, `429` (auth/rate limit in mock mode)\n  - `favicon`, `ERR_CONNECTION_REFUSED`, `Failed to fetch`, `NetworkError`\n  - Fails test if non-filtered errors are detected\n\n### 8. **Test Patterns**\n\n**routes.spec.ts** — Simple baseline captures:\n```typescript\ntest(\"close call page\", async ({ stablePage }) => {\n  await stablePage.goto(\"/close-call\");\n  await expect(stablePage).toHaveScreenshot(\"close-call.png\", { fullPage: true });\n});\n```\n\n**states.spec.ts** — Complex interaction scenarios:\n```typescript\n// Example: Wallet connection flow\ntest(\"wallet connected\", async ({ stablePage }) => {\n  await stablePage.addInitScript(() => {\n    localStorage.removeItem(\"rng-utopia-mock-wallet\");\n  });\n  await stablePage.goto(\"/\");\n  \n  // Click wallet connect button\n  await stablePage.locator(\".rng-wallet-button--disconnected\").click();\n  \n  // Wait for connected state\n  await stablePage.waitForSelector(\".rng-wallet-button--connected\", { timeout: 5000 });\n  \n  // Re-inject animation freeze (navigation clears it)\n  await stablePage.addStyleTag({ content: FREEZE_CSS });\n  \n  // Settle UI\n  await stablePage.waitForTimeout(300);\n  \n  await expect(stablePage).toHaveScreenshot(\"home-connected.png\", { fullPage: true });\n});\n```\n\n**Pattern for tolerance (SVG variance):**\n```typescript\nawait expect(stablePage).toHaveScreenshot(\"profile-connected.png\", {\n  fullPage: true,\n  maxDiffPixelRatio: 0.03,  # 3% tolerance for avatar SVG sub-pixel rendering\n});\n```\n\n### 9. **Existing Close-Call Baselines**\n\n- **Route baseline**: `close-call.png` captured (shows disconnected, full page)\n- **Last updated**: 2026-03-10\n- **Missing**: No state variants (disconnected/connected, interactions, error states, game states)\n\n### 10. **Naming Conventions**\n\n**Test names:** Descriptive, kebab-case in fixture names\n- `\"close call page\"` → filename `close-call.png`\n- `\"wallet connected\"` → filename `{page}-connected.png`\n- `\"wallet disconnected\"` → filename `{page}-disconnected.png`\n- `\"error toast below middle container\"` → filename `coinflip-error-toast-position.png`\n\n**Fixtures:** Descriptive, include context in names\n- `home-connected.png` (home page + wallet connected)\n- `lotr-tier-selected.png` (Lord of RNGs + round selected state)\n- `lotr-lobby-disconnected.png` (Lord of RNGs lobby + disconnected)\n\n### Key Files and Paths\n\n- **Visual tests**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/visual/routes.spec.ts`\n- **State tests**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/visual/states.spec.ts`\n- **Fixtures**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/fixtures.ts`\n- **Config**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/playwright.config.ts`\n- **Snapshots**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/__snapshots__/visual/`\n- **Close-Call baseline**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/__snapshots__/visual/routes.spec.ts/close-call.png`"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ab5cfa265547eaca4 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 51030\ntool_uses: 26\nduration_ms: 72912</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3203ecf8-5327-4c6a-a3f1-03636bd6e7bf","uuid":"477ae762-0938-43b7-a24f-d26b2d2079d2","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the visual test setup in the rng-utopia project. I need to understand:\n1. Where are visual tests located? Check `e2e/visual/` directory structure\n2. What test runner is used (playwright? something else)?\n3. Where are baselines stored?\n4. How does `pnpm test:visual` and `pnpm test:visual:update` work?\n5. Are there any existing close-call visual tests?\n6. What's the test configuration?\n\nLook in:\n- sources/rng-utopia/e2e/visual/\n- sources/rng-utopia/package.json (for test:visual scripts)\n- sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/package.json\n- Any playwright config files\n\nBe thorough - check naming conventions, existing test patterns, and how baselines are organized.","agentId":"ab5cfa265547eaca4","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have all the informati