{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01W1oVvLDGY6k672bAvcK4Hb","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I've found the issue. Let me create a comprehensive summary of the findings.\n\n## Summary: Why Close-Call Visual Tests Show Identical Results\n\n### Root Cause\n\nThe visual tests produce identical output despite the context rewrite because **the backend API calls fail silently with no fallback or mock data**, resulting in:\n- `currentRound = null`\n- `recentCandles = []`\n- `loading` state remains `true` indefinitely in the UI\n\n### Evidence\n\n#### 1. **CloseCallContext.tsx** — Backend API with no fallback (lines 111-134)\n```typescript\nasync function fetchCurrentRound(): Promise<Round | null> {\n  try {\n    const res = await fetch(`${FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL}/closecall/current-round`);\n    if (!res.ok) return null;  // ← Returns null on error\n    const data = (await res.json()) as { BackendRoundResponse | null };\n    if (!data.round) return null;  // ← Returns null if no round\n    return backendToRound(data.round);\n  } catch {\n    return null;  // ← Silently catches all errors, returns null\n  }\n}\n```\n\nWhen `VITE_FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL` is not set, defaults to `http://127.0.0.1:3100`, which doesn't exist in visual test mode. The fetch fails, caught exception returns `null`, no data, no error thrown.\n\n#### 2. **Visual Test Configuration** (playwright.config.ts, line 44-46)\n```typescript\nwebServer: {\n  env: {\n    VITE_MOCK_MODE: \"true\",\n  },\n}\n```\n\nVisual tests run with `VITE_MOCK_MODE=true`, which enables the MockWalletProvider (for wallet simulation) but **does not provide any mock data for the close-call backend API calls**.\n\n#### 3. **CloseCallPage.tsx** — \"Loading...\" State (lines 235-246)\n```typescript\n{!loading && recentCandles.length > 0 ? (\n  <CandlestickChart\n    candles={recentCandles}\n    currentPrice={currentPrice}\n    progress={candleProgress}\n  />\n) : (\n  <div className=\"close-call-main__loading\">\n    <div className=\"close-call-main__spinner\" />\n    <span>Loading chart...</span>\n  </div>\n)}\n```\n\nWhen `loading=true` or `recentCandles=[]`, the page shows the loading spinner indefinitely. The `loading` state is only set to `false` after the first `poll()` call (line 407), but if `fetchCurrentRound()` returns `null`, the UI remains in loading state.\n\n#### 4. **No Mock Data Provider**\n- There is **no mock-data fallback** in CloseCallContext\n- Other features (e.g., `player-profile/`, `boss-raid/`) have `mock-simulation.ts` files, but close-call has none\n- The context does not check for `VITE_MOCK_MODE` to provide synthetic round data\n- The price subscription (`usePriceSubscription(\"BTC\")`) may also fail or return 0 in mock mode if the price-feeds package has no mock implementation\n\n#### 5. **Error Handling** (fixtures.ts, lines 28-37)\nThe visual test fixture filters out expected noise:\n```typescript\nconst NOISE_PATTERNS = [\n  \"401\",                 // JWT auth attempts in mock mode (no backend)\n  \"403\",                 // Auth rejection in mock mode\n  \"429\",                 // Rate limit\n  \"favicon\",             // Missing favicon\n  \"ERR_CONNECTION_REFUSED\", // Backend not running in visual test mode\n  \"Failed to fetch\",     // ← Close-call API failures are filtered!\n  \"Failed to load resource\",\n  \"NetworkError\",\n];\n```\n\nThe \"Failed to fetch\" errors from the API calls are suppressed, so tests pass without showing that the backend is completely unavailable.\n\n### What Hasn't Changed Visually\n\n1. **Same loading state**: Both old (mock-simulation.ts) and new (backend API) contexts show \"Loading chart...\" when data is unavailable\n2. **Same sidebar**: Disconnected wallet button, bet amount input, pool info — all render the same\n3. **Same absence of round data**: No candles, no prices, no betting UI\n\n### Why the Snapshots Are Identical\n\nThe old `mock-simulation.ts` approach (if it existed) would have provided synthetic data to the context, showing live candles, prices, and bet UI. The new approach provides **nothing**, leaving the page in the same \"loading\" visual state as an empty, uninitialized page.\n\n### Files Involved\n\n| File | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/close-call/context/CloseCallContext.tsx` | Backend API client with no fallback on failure |\n| `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/close-call/CloseCallPage.tsx` | UI component that enters infinite loading state when data is null |\n| `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/playwright.config.ts` | Visual test config sets `VITE_MOCK_MODE=true` but no backend mocking |\n| `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/fixtures.ts` | Test fixture filters out \"Failed to fetch\" errors |\n\n### Recommendations\n\n1. **Add mock data fallback** to CloseCallContext when `VITE_MOCK_MODE=true` or API calls fail\n2. **Provide synthetic round data** similar to how other features use `mock-simulation.ts`\n3. **Or**: Mock the fetch calls in visual test setup to return consistent test data\n4. **Or**: Start a mock backend server during visual tests (similar to how local E2E tests work)"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a915164754b4f0402 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 76194\ntool_uses: 34\nduration_ms: 74117</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3203ecf8-5327-4c6a-a3f1-03636bd6e7bf","uuid":"e498c3e7-c1ff-4e6d-8ed4-ea3100ba761c","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand why the close-call page looks identical in visual tests despite major context changes (mock-simulation.ts was deleted, context rewritten to use backend API). Visual tests run with VITE_MOCK_MODE=true.\n\nCheck:\n1. `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/close-call/context/CloseCallContext.tsx` — what happens when backend API calls fail (no backend in mock mode)? Does it fall back to mock data?\n2. `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/close-call/CloseCallPage.tsx` — does it have a mock mode check? Does it show mock data regardless of context?\n3. Is there a mock wrapper or provider that intercepts in mock mode?\n4. Check `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/close-call/` for any files that still provide mock data\n\nFocus on understanding why the visual output hasn't changed despite the context rewrite.","agentId":"a915164754b4f0402","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I've found the issue. Let me create a comprehensive summary of the findings.\n\n## Summary: Why Close-Call Visual Tests Show Identical Results\n\n### Root Cause\n\nThe visual tests produce identical output despite the context rewrite because **the backend API calls fail silently with no fallback or mock data**, resulting in:\n- `currentRound = null`\n- `recentCandles = []`\n- `loading` state remains `true` indefinitely in the UI\n\n### Evidence\n\n#### 1. **CloseCallContext.tsx** — Backend API with no fallback (lines 111-134)\n```typescript\nasync function fetchCurrentRound(): Promise<Round | null> {\n  try {\n    const res = await fetch(`${FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL}/closecall/current-round`);\n    if (!res.ok) return null;  // ← Returns null on error\n    const data = (await res.json()) as { BackendRoundResponse | null };\n    if (!data.round) return null;  // ← Returns null if no round\n    return backendToRound(data.round);\n  } catch {\n    return null;  // ← Silently catches all errors, returns null\n  }\n}\n```\n\nWhen `VITE_FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL` is not set, defaults to `http://127.0.0.1:3100`, which doesn't exist in visual test mode. The fetch fails, caught exception returns `null`, no data, no error thrown.\n\n#### 2. **Visual Test Configuration** (playwright.config.ts, line 44-46)\n```typescript\nwebServer: {\n  env: {\n    VITE_MOCK_MODE: \"true\",\n  },\n}\n```\n\nVisual tests run with `VITE_MOCK_MODE=true`, which enables the MockWalletProvider (for wallet simulation) but **does not provide any mock data for the close-call backend API calls**.\n\n#### 3. **CloseCallPage.tsx** — \"Loading...\" State (lines 235-246)\n```typescript\n{!loading && recentCandles.length > 0 ? (\n  <CandlestickChart\n    candles={recentCandles}\n    currentPrice={currentPrice}\n    progress={candleProgress}\n  />\n) : (\n  <div className=\"close-call-main__loading\">\n    <div className=\"close-call-main__spinner\" />\n    <span>Loading chart...</span>\n  </div>\n)}\n```\n\nWhen `loading=true` or `recentCandles=[]`, the page shows the loading spinner indefinitely. The `loading` state is only set to `false` after the first `poll()` call (line 407), but if `fetchCurrentRound()` returns `null`, the UI remains in loading state.\n\n#### 4. **No Mock Data Provider**\n- There is **no mock-data fallback** in CloseCallContext\n- Other features (e.g., `player-profile/`, `boss-raid/`) have `mock-simulation.ts` files, but close-call has none\n- The context does not check for `VITE_MOCK_MODE` to provide synthetic round data\n- The price subscription (`usePriceSubscription(\"BTC\")`) may also fail or return 0 in mock mode if the price-feeds package has no mock implementation\n\n#### 5. **Error Handling** (fixtures.ts, lines 28-37)\nThe visual test fixture filters out expected noise:\n```typescript\nconst NOISE_PATTERNS = [\n  \"401\",                 // JWT auth attempts in mock mode (no backend)\n  \"403\",                 // Auth rejection in mock mode\n  \"429\",                 // Rate limit\n  \"favicon\",             // Missing favicon\n  \"ERR_CONNECTION_REFUSED\", // Backend not running in visual test mode\n  \"Failed to fetch\",     // ← Close-call API failures are filtered!\n  \"Failed to load resource\",\n  \"NetworkError\",\n];\n```\n\nThe \"Failed to fetch\" errors from the API calls are suppressed, so tests pass without showing that the backend is completely unavailable.\n\n### What Hasn't Changed Visually\n\n1. **Same loading state**: Both old (mock-simulation.ts) and new (backend API) contexts show \"Loading chart...\" when data is unavailable\n2. **Same sidebar**: Disconnected wallet button, bet amount input, pool info — all render the same\n3. **Same absence of round data**: No candles, no prices, no betting UI\n\n### Why the Snapshots Are Identical\n\nThe old `mock-simulation.ts` approach (if it existed) would have provided synthetic data to the context, showing live candles, prices, and bet UI. The new approach provides **nothing**, leaving the page in the same \"loading\" visual state as an empty, uninitialized page.\n\n### Files Involved\n\n| File | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/close-call/context/CloseCallContext.tsx` | Backend API client with no fallback on failure |\n| `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/close-call/CloseCallPage.tsx` | UI component that enters infinite loading state when data is null |\n| `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/playwright.config.ts` | Visual test config sets `VITE_MOCK_MODE=true` but no backend mocking |\n| `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/fixtures.ts` | Test fixture filters out \"Failed to fetch\" errors |\n\n### Recommendations\n\n1. **Add mock data fallback** to CloseCallContext when `VITE_MOCK_MODE=true` or API calls fail\n2. **Provide synthetic round data** similar to how other features use `mock-simulation.ts`\n3. **Or**: Mock the fetch calls in visual test setup to return consistent test data\n4. **Or**: Start a mock backend server during visual tests (similar to how local E2E tests work)"}],"totalDurationMs":74117,"totalTokens":76194,"totalToolUseCount":34,"usage":{"input_tokens":235,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1273,"cache_read_input_tokens":73236,"output_tokens":1450,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requ